<TEXT>
<P>
We were disgusted to hear that CBS dropped "The Van Dyke Show" and "Annie 
McGuire." First, they put them opposite stiff competition, then dumped them 
because of low ratings. We had to tape them for viewing at a later date since 
they were opposite our favorite shows. Why schedule shows in time slots where 
they are bound to fail? 
</P>
<P>
Ira Bowman, Los Angeles 
</P>
