<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: CAMERA ANGLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Leonard Klady 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sources tell us that Kevin Costner will make his directorial debut in March 
when Island Pics shoots "Dances With Wolves" in Mexico. The 19th-Century 
romantic adventure, adapted by Michael Blake from his novel, centers on the 
relationship between a white man and an Indian woman in the Southwest. 
</P>
<P>
Reps for Costner and Island wouldn't comment. 
</P>
<P>
A source said that Costner, who's been searching for a project to direct for 
about a year, zeroed in on "Wolves" partly because it could be made 
economically. He'll have the only major English-speaking role, with the other 
principal parts written in Indian and Spanish dialects. 
</P>
<P>
Also signing up for his first directing job is "Moonstruck" writer John Patrick 
Shanley. The project is "Joe vs. the Volcano" at Warner Bros., a comic fantasy 
with Tom Hanks as a man who sells his soul to the devil. Scheduled to shoot 
next summer. Leonard Klady 
</P>
</TEXT>
