<HEADLINE>
<P>
A J.F.K. OBSESSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lee Green's story about David Lifton's work ("His J.F.K. Obsession," Nov. 20) 
was a real page-turner. Green pointed out that Lifton's book, "Best Evidence," 
was given a negative review by Times' critic Kenneth John Atchity, who felt 
that getting to the truth of the matter won't resurrect J.F.K. I say, the point 
is not to resurrect J.F.K.; that cannot be done. However, we should not let 
whoever assassinated him get away with murder. 
</P>
<P>
MONICA WELLESLEY 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
