<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK GOLDSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RATTLES AND HUMS: Motley Crue is apparently still at work on its upcoming 
album, "Too Hot to Handle." In addition to the title track, the band has loads 
of originals like "Dollar in My Pocket," "Poisonous Dreams" and "Dead Man" -- 
plus a raucous cover of "California Girls". . . . Iron Maiden is taking a year 
off from recording while singer Bruce Dickenson finishes a novel about a 
transvestite. . . . Talk about a real Richard Thompson fan: John Mellencamp 
drummer Kenny Aronoff called to get tickets to a recent Thompson show in 
Bloomington, Ind., only to find that the concert had been canceled after 
Thompson's drummer slipped in the shower and broke his arm. Aronoff offered to 
fill in and not only played that night, but also finished out the tour with 
Thompson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
