<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. WORKERS, NOT CORPORATE RAIDERS, ARE INDISPENSABLE TO NATION'S ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Archimedes said that if he had "a lever long enough and a prop strong enough," 
he could move the Earth. 
</P>
<P>
Evidently, some ingenious financiers have found that lever (the modern word is 
leverage) in the form of junk bonds, and they certainly have created giant 
movement in the commercial world. 
</P>
<P>
One hopes that these operators will avoid the element of greed and work toward 
improving our national economy. 
</P>
<P>
SAMUEL S. ZIPSER 
</P>
<P>
Oceanside 
</P>
</TEXT>
