<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIVING NORMANDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read Dirlam's story on Normandy and, realizing the article was meant to 
promote travel to Normandy and was not a history lesson, it was a nice job. 
However, not only the 1st Infantry Division landed on "Bloody Omaha Beach," but 
so did the 115th and 116th regiments of the 29th Infantry Division. They 
suffered even heavier losses than the 1st Division. I did not serve with the 
29th in 1944, but in 1962. I am writing because the above is rarely told in 
articles about D-day. 
</P>
<P>
BRUCE H. ROUSH Jr. 
</P>
<P>
Jarrettsville, Md. 
</P>
</TEXT>
