<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Embassy Suites Hotel Under WayNear airport -- An October, 1989, 
completion is scheduled for the $27.6-million, 215-suite Embassy Suites Hotel 
under construction at 9801 Airport Blvd., near Los Angeles International 
Airport. The developer is KOAR-LAX Embassy Investment Partnership, whose 
managing partner -- KOAR Inc. -- is a Los Angeles-based development firm 
specializing in joint ventures with Japanese and other Asian investors. The 
architect is Carl Wahlquist, designer of 30 Embassy Suite hotels, and the 
general contractor is McDevitt &amp; Street Co. Continental Illinois National 
Bank &amp; Trust Co., Chicago, supplied $20 million in construction financing. 
Hotel will be second Embassy Suites in airport area; there is one in El 
Segundo. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
