<HEADLINE>
<P>
AIDS FOUNDATION HONORS FIRM FOR DESIGN SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The architectural firm of Johannes Van Tilburg &amp; Partners has been honored 
with the AIDS Hospice Foundation's Heart of Gold Award for design services for 
a new hospice opened in December at 2000 Stadium Way. 
</P>
<P>
Named for AIDS activist Chris Brownlie, a member of the foundation's board of 
directors, the new facility is the largest of its kind in the country and 
offers the most comprehensive care and services. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to contributing the design, the architectural firm coordinated the 
work of consultants, including interior designer Millicent Grappell, Jitu Mehta 
&amp; Associates Structural Engineers, Dalan Engineering Electrical Engineers, 
and Sanjar &amp; Associates Mechanical Engineers, who also donated their 
services. 
</P>
