<P>
FOUR CALIFORNIA HOTELS NAMED AMONG 10 BEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four California hotels -- in Los Angeles, Santa Barbara, Century City and San 
Diego -- are among the top 10 best new hotels in the world, according to Travel 
&amp; Leisure magazine. 
</P>
<P>
The JW Marriott at Century City, a 375-room, 17-story hotel, was singled out by 
writer Paul B. Finney in the magazine's December, 1988, issue, as deserving "an 
Academy Award for 'Best Performance by a Major Chain."' 
</P>
<P>
Other hotels on the list: Regent Beverly Wilshire, Los Angeles; Four Seasons 
Biltmore, Santa Barbara; Le Meridien, San Diego; Westin Kauai, Hawaii; Hyatt 
Regency Waikoloa, Hawaii; Grand Floridian, Walt Disney World, Florida; 
Royalton, New York City; Hotel 21 East, Chicago, and Club Med, Huatulco, 
Mexico. 
