<HEADLINE>
<P>
FENCING, GATING CEREMONIES SET AT PARK LABREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forest City Enterprises, the Cleveland-based owners of Park Labrea, and its 
management will hold ground-breaking ceremonies on Thursday at 9 a.m. for the 
fencing and gating improvement project at Park Labrea. 
</P>
<P>
The improvements, expected to exceed $1 million, will provide the 176-acre park 
with three main manned guard entrances at 6th Street and Curson Avenue, 3rd 
Street and Burnside Avenue and an entry from Hauser Boulevard for the adjoining 
eastern sector. 
</P>
<P>
The park consists of 1,499 garden units and 18 high-rises, with 153 apartments 
in each building, and houses about 10,000 residents. 
</P>
