LARRY HULL HEADS APARTMENT ASSN. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Larry A. Hull, a Santa Clara-based property manager and real estate investment 
analyst, has been elected president of the California Apartment Assn., 
succeeding John West of Covina. 
</P>
<P>
Other officers are Hugh Smith, retired retail executive, Pasadena, 
president-elect; John Alioto, senior vice president, the Walters Management 
Co., San Diego, vice president; Dwight Long, president, Tri-Cal Investment 
&amp; Management Co., Fresno, secretary, and Robert A. Diaz, president, Capital 
West Real Estate &amp; Investment, Orange County, treasurer. 
</P>
