<TEXT>
<P>
Police arrested anti-abortion activists in Worcester, Mass., and Wichita, Kan. 
In Worcester, 92 abortion protesters who blocked doorways and jammed elevators 
at the Planned Parenthood League of Massachusetts clinic were charged with 
trespassing and released on their own recognizance, officials said. Another 50 
