<TEXT>
<P>
Forty-eight inmates in a San Jose jail locked themselves back in their cells 
after the lone correctional officer passed out because of a suspected virus. 
The prisoners then used an emergency phone to call for someone to help her. The 
men were rewarded with ice cream at their next meal for following correct 
emergency procedure, shown during a jail orientation film, according to Jail 
Cmdr. Bob Conroy. 
</P>
