SOUTH BAY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
WORK STARTED ON MEDICAL BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has started on a $13-million medical office building at AMI South 
Bay Hospital in Redondo Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-story structure, to be completed in December, will accommodate 40 
physicians in 46,000 square feet of rental space. The major tenant will be the 
South Bay Family Medical Group. The building will be the second medical office 
structure on the hospital grounds. A smaller building houses 30 physicians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
