<HEADLINE>
<P>
AKIHITO'S ELDEST SON IS NEXT IN LINE FOR JAPANESE THRONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the death Saturday of Emperor Hirohito and the ascension of Crown Prince 
Akihito to the Chrysanthemum Throne, the person next in line to succeed to the 
Japanese throne is Crown Prince Naruhito, 28, formerly known as Prince Hiro, 
eldest son of Akihito. 
</P>
<P>
Other heirs to the throne in order are Prince Aya, 23, second son of Akihito; 
Prince Hitachi, 53, second son of Hirohito, and Prince Mikasa, 73, youngest 
brother of Hirohito. 
</P>
<P>
Hirohito's widow, Nagako, 85, now the empress dowager, is suffering from hip 
trouble and has not appeared in public for several years. Palace officials made 
no mention of her on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
